data.title: List of acts of the Parliament of the United Kingdom from 1882
data.text:
Short title, or popular nameCitationRoyal assent (or the start of session)Long title

45 & 46 Vict. c. 1

13 March 1882

An Act to apply the sum of Three hundred and thirteen thousand two hundred and seventy pounds out of the Consolidated Fund to the service of the year ending on the thirty-first day of March one thousand eight hundred and eighty-two.

(Repealed by Statute Law Revision Act 1898)

45 & 46 Vict. c. 2

13 March 1882

An Act to authorise the use of Reply Post Cards.

(Repealed by Post Office Act 1908)

45 & 46 Vict. c. 3

29 March 1882

An Act to amend the Law relating to the use of Gunpowder in Slate Mines.

45 & 46 Vict. c. 4

29 March 1882

An Act to apply certain sums out of the Consolidated Fund to the service of the years ending on the thirty-first day of March one thousand eight hundred and eighty-one, one thousand eight hundred and eighty-two, and one thousand eight hundred and eighty-three.

(Repealed by Statute Law Revision Act 1898)

45 & 46 Vict. c. 5

21 April 1882

An Act to enable Her Majesty to provide for the Establishment of His Royal Highness the Duke of Albany and Her Serene Highness Princess Helen Frederica Augusta of Waldeck and Pyrmont, and to settle an Annuity on Her Serene Highness.

45 & 46 Vict. c. 6

28 April 1882

An Act to amend the law in regard to householders under the General Police and Improvement Acts in Scotland.

(Repealed by Burgh Police (Scotland) Act 1892)

45 & 46 Vict. c. 7

28 April 1882

An Act to provide, during twelve months, for the Discipline and Regulation of the Army.

45 & 46 Vict. c. 8

19 May 1882

An Act to apply the sum of nine million two hundred and eighty-two thousand four hundred and thirty-five pounds out of the Consolidated Fund to the service of the year ending on the thirty-first day of March one thousand eight hundred and eighty-three.

(Repealed by Statute Law Revision Act 1898)

45 & 46 Vict. c. 9

19 June 1882

An Act to amend the Documentary Evidence Act 1868, and other enactments relating to the evidence of documents by means of copies printed by the Government Printers.

45 & 46 Vict. c. 10

19 June 1882

An Act for making provision for facilitating the Manoeuvres of Troops to be assembled during the present Summer.

(Repealed by Statute Law Revision Act 1898)

45 & 46 Vict. c. 11

19 June 1882

An Act to amend the Public Health (Scotland) Act, 1867.[a]

45 & 46 Vict. c. 12

19 June 1882

An Act to amend the Law relating to the application of moneys arising from the sale of Militia Storehouses.

(Repealed by Reserve Forces Act 1980)

45 & 46 Vict. c. 13

19 June 1882

An Act for the Improvement of Arklow Harbour.

45 & 46 Vict. c. 14

19 June 1882

An Act to confer further powers upon the Metropolitan Board of Works with respect to Streets and Buildings in the Metropolis.

(Repealed by London Building Act 1894 (57 & 58 Vict. c. ccxiii))

45 & 46 Vict. c. 15

19 June 1882

An Act to provide for the better application of Moneys paid by way of Compensation for the compulsory acquisition of Common Lands and extinguishment of Rights of Common.

45 & 46 Vict. c. 16

19 June 1882

An Act to amend the Irish Reproductive Loan Fund Act, 1874.[b]

45 & 46 Vict. c. 17

3 July 1882

An Act for the transfer of Property in Ireland held for the Service of Her Majesty's Customs and of the Inland Revenue to the Commissioners of Public Works in Ireland; and for other purposes relating thereto.

45 & 46 Vict. c. 18

3 July 1882

An Act to regulate the procedure of School Boards in Scotland in the dismissal of Teachers.

45 & 46 Vict. c. 19

3 July 1882

An Act to amend the law relating to the interment of any person found felo de se.

(Repealed by Suicide Act 1961)

45 & 46 Vict. c. 20

3 July 1882

An Act to amend the Poor Rate Assessment and Collection Act, 1869.[c]

45 & 46 Vict. c. 21

12 July 1882

An Act to amend the Places of Worship Sites Act, 1873.[d]

45 & 46 Vict. c. 22

12 July 1882

An Act to make better provision for Inquiries with regard to Boiler Explosions.

45 & 46 Vict. c. 23

12 July 1882

An Act to extend the Public Health Act, 1875,[e] to the making of Byelaws for Fruit Pickers.

45 & 46 Vict. c. 24

12 July 1882

An Act to amend the Petty Sessions (Ireland) Act, 1851.[f]

45 & 46 Vict. c. 25

12 July 1882

An Act for the prevention of Crime in Ireland.

(Repealed by Statute Law Revision Act 1898)

45 & 46 Vict. c. 26

12 July 1882

An Act to amend the Law relating to the Election of Lords Temporal to serve in Parliament for Ireland.

45 & 46 Vict. c. 27

12 July 1882

An Act to extend certain Provisions of the Poor Rate Assessment and Collection Act, 1869,[c] to the Highway Rate, and for other purposes.

(Repealed by Statute Law (Repeals) Act 1973)

45 & 46 Vict. c. 28

24 July 1882

An Act to apply the sum of five million seven hundred and three thousand eight hundred and ninety-one pounds out of the Consolidated Fund to the service of the year ending on the thirty-first day of March one thousand eight hundred and eighty-three.

(Repealed by Statute Law Revision Act 1898)

45 & 46 Vict. c. 29

24 July 1882

An Act to amend the Acts relating to the County Courts in Ireland, and to make better provision for Appeals under the said Acts.

45 & 46 Vict. c. 30

24 July 1882

An Act to amend the Baths and Wash Houses Acts.

45 & 46 Vict. c. 31

24 July 1882

An Act to render Judgments obtained in certain Inferior Courts in England, Scotland, and Ireland respectively, effectual in any other part of the United Kingdom.

45 & 46 Vict. c. 32

24 July 1882

An Act for the acquisition of Property and the provision of new Buildings for the Admiralty and War Office.

45 & 46 Vict. c. 33

10 August 1882

An Act further to amend the Acts relating to the raising of Money by the Metropolitan Board of Works; and for other purposes.

45 & 46 Vict. c. 34

10 August 1882

An Act to amend "The Beer Dealers' Retail Licences Act, 1880."[g]

45 & 46 Vict. c. 35

10 August 1882

An Act to amend so much of "The Friendly Societies Act, 1875,"[h] as relates to quinquennial returns of sickness and mortality.

(Repealed by Friendly Societies Act 1887)

45 & 46 Vict. c. 36

10 August 1882

An Act to amend the Pauper Inmates Discharge and Regulation Act, 1871.[i]

45 & 46 Vict. c. 37

10 August 1882

An Act to amend the Law respecting the obtaining of Corn Returns.

(Repealed by the Agriculture and Horticulture Development Board Order 2008 (SI 2008/576))

45 & 46 Vict. c. 38

10 August 1882

An Act for facilitating sales, leases, and other dispositions of settled land, and for promoting the execution of improvements thereon.

45 & 46 Vict. c. 39

10 August 1882

An Act for further improving the Practice of Conveyancing; and for other purposes.

45 & 46 Vict. c. 40

10 August 1882

An Act to amend the law of Copyright relating to Musical Compositions.

45 & 46 Vict. c. 41

10 August 1882

An Act to grant certain Duties of Customs and Inland Revenue, to alter other Duties, and to amend the Laws relating to Customs and Inland Revenue.

45 & 46 Vict. c. 42

18 August 1882

An Act to amend the Law relating to Civil Imprisonment in Scotland.

Bills of Sale Act (1878) Amendment Act 1882

or the Bills of Sale Act 1882

45 & 46 Vict. c. 43

18 August 1882

An Act to amend the Bills of Sale Act, 1878.[j]

45 & 46 Vict. c. 44

18 August 1882

An Act to authorise the Commutation of a portion of a Pension in pursuance of the Pensions Commutation Act, 1871.[k]

45 & 46 Vict. c. 45

18 August 1882

An Act to make provision for the transfer of the Assets and Liabilities of the Provident Branch of the Bombay Civil Fund and other funds to the Secretary of State for India in Council.

45 & 46 Vict. c. 46

18 August 1882

An Act to amend the Isle of Man (Officers) Act, 1876.[l]

45 & 46 Vict. c. 47

18 August 1882

An Act to make provision respecting certain Arrears of Rent in Ireland.

45 & 46 Vict. c. 48

18 August 1882

An Act to consolidate the Acts relating to the Reserve Forces.

45 & 46 Vict. c. 49

18 August 1882

An Act to consolidate the Acts relating to the Militia.

(Repealed by Reserve Forces Act 1980)

45 & 46 Vict. c. 50

18 August 1882

An Act for consolidating, with Amendments, enactments relating to Municipal Corporations in England and Wales.

45 & 46 Vict. c. 51

18 August 1882

An Act to extend the Acts relating to the purchase of small Government Annuities and to assuring payments of money on death.

45 & 46 Vict. c. 52

18 August 1882

An Act to continue certain Turnpike Acts, and to repeal certain other Turnpike Acts; and for other purposes connected therewith.

45 & 46 Vict. c. 53

18 August 1882

An Act to amend the Law of Entail in Scotland.

45 & 46 Vict. c. 54

18 August 1882

An Act to amend the Artizans and Labourers Dwellings Acts.

(Repealed by Housing of the Working Classes Act 1890)

45 & 46 Vict. c. 55

18 August 1882

An Act to amend the Law with respect to the Charges on and Payments to the Mercantile Marine Fund, and to Expenses of Prosecutions for Offences committed at Sea.

45 & 46 Vict. c. 56

18 August 1882

An Act to facilitate and regulate the supply of Electricity for Lighting and other purposes in Great Britain and Ireland.

(Repealed by Electricity Act 1989)

45 & 46 Vict. c. 57

18 August 1882

An Act to amend the law relating to Costs and Salaries in County Courts.

(Repealed by County Courts Act 1888)

45 & 46 Vict. c. 58

18 August 1882

An Act to amend the Divided Parishes and Poor Law Amendment Act, 1876;[m] and for other purposes.

45 & 46 Vict. c. 59

18 August 1882

An Act to reorganise the Educational Endowments of Scotland.

45 & 46 Vict. c. 60

18 August 1882

An Act to amend and extend the provisions of the Land Law (Ireland) Act, 1881,[n] relating to Labourers' Cottages and Allotments.

45 & 46 Vict. c. 61

18 August 1882

An Act to codify the law relating to Bills of Exchange, Cheques, and Promissory Notes.

45 & 46 Vict. c. 62

18 August 1882

An Act to grant Money for the purpose of Loans by the Public Works Loan Commissioners and the Commissioners of Public Works in Ireland and the Irish Land Commission; and for other purposes relating to Loans by those Commissioners.

(Repealed by Statute Law (Repeals) Act 2004)

45 & 46 Vict. c. 63

18 August 1882

An Act to amend the Acts regulating the pay of certain officers of the Royal Irish Constabulary Force, and for other purposes connected therewith.

45 & 46 Vict. c. 64

18 August 1882

An Act to continue various expiring Laws.

(Repealed by Statute Law Revision Act 1898)

45 & 46 Vict. c. 65

18 August 1882

An Act to make provision respecting certain Prison Charities.

45 & 46 Vict. c. 66

18 August 1882

An Act to amend the Law relating to Licences to retail Intoxicating Liquors on Passenger Vessels in Scotland.

45 & 46 Vict. c. 67

18 August 1882

An Act to further amend the Law relating to Turnpike Roads in South Wales.

(Repealed by Highways Act 1959 (7 & 8 Eliz. 2. c. 25))

45 & 46 Vict. c. 68

18 August 1882

An Act to suspend for a limited period, on account of Corrupt Practices, the holding of an Election of a Member or Members to serve in Parliament for certain cities and boroughs.

(Repealed by Statute Law Revision Act 1898)

45 & 46 Vict. c. 69

18 August 1882

An Act to amend the Intermediate Education (Ireland) Act, 1878.[o]

45 & 46 Vict. c. 70

18 August 1882

An Act to amend the Supreme Court of Judicature Act (Ireland), 1877.[p]

45 & 46 Vict. c. 71

18 August 1882

An Act to apply a sum out of the Consolidated Fund to the service of the year ending on the thirty-first day of March one thousand eight hundred and eighty-three, and to appropriate the Supplies granted in this Session of Parliament.

(Repealed by Statute Law Revision Act 1898)

45 & 46 Vict. c. 72

18 August 1882

An Act for amending the Laws relating to Customs and Inland Revenue, and Postage and other Stamps, and for making further provision respecting the National Debt and charges payable out of the public revenue or by the Commissioners for the Reduction of the National Debt; and for other purposes.

45 & 46 Vict. c. 73

18 August 1882

An Act for the better protection of Ancient Monuments.

45 & 46 Vict. c. 74

18 August 1882

An Act to amend the Post Office Acts with respect to the Conveyance of Parcels.

45 & 46 Vict. c. 75

18 August 1882

An Act to consolidate and amend the Acts relating to the Property of Married Women.

45 & 46 Vict. c. 76

18 August 1882

An Act to amend the Merchant Shipping Acts, 1854 to 1880, with respect to Colonial Courts of Inquiry.

(Repealed by Merchant Shipping Act 1894)

45 & 46 Vict. c. 77

18 August 1882

An Act to amend the law of Citation in Scotland.

45 & 46 Vict. c. 78

18 August 1882

An Act to establish a Fishery Board for Scotland.

45 & 46 Vict. c. 79

18 August 1882

An Act to make provision for the arrangement of Accounts between the Commissioners of Her Majesty's Treasury and the Secretary of State in Council of India in respect of certain Home Charges for Her Majestys Forces serving in India.

(Repealed by Statute Law Revision Act 1898)

45 & 46 Vict. c. 80

18 August 1882

An Act for the Extension of Allotments.

(Repealed by Statute Law (Repeals) Act 1993)

45 & 46 Vict. c. 81

18 August 1882

An Act for disannexing the Rectory of Somersham from the office of Regius Professor of Divinity in the University of Cambridge, and for making better provision for the cure of Souls within the said Rectory; and for other purposes.

45 & 46 Vict. c. 82

18 August 1882

An Act for amending the Lunacy Regulation Acts.

(Repealed by Lunacy Act 1890)
